ill) radius, respectively. The surface density has a peak in these\nregions due to the balance between centrifugal force and gravity of the\nprotoplanet. The size of these disks corresponds well to the outermost orbit of\nregular satellites around Jupiter and Saturn. Regular satellites may form in\nsuch compact disks around proto-gas giant planets.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 15 Oct 2008 02:14:23 GMT"}],"update_date":"2008-10-16"}
